            <subject>Re: Slide 3 - Integral Action</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;There are two ways of looking at the equation $$x_I(k+1)=x_I(k) + e(k)$$:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At steady state, the state instant k+1 is equal to the state at k and hence, the error term e becomes zero.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you write this recursively, you will see the error adding up, just as it happens in integral mode.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</message>
